<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">People are saying you should not be able to use the epic weapon untill 56+. Althouh this would limit a small amount of people doing the epic quest, do you think its a level 55 and below clerics fault Verant named the effect the same name as the spell we get at 56? What if it was still a 96% res but had a new name that no other spell had. Would people still be saying this? No. Sorry it just doesnt seem right, I got my epic at level 54, just because the effect was named the same thing as a spell other clerics cant use till 56+ shouldnt mean I am not worthy of it.
   The mage epic pet is more powerful than a lvl 60 mages pet. For the mage epic is a lvl 46 spell, should a level 60 magician with no epic be slightly jelous of lets say a 55 mage with epic? Probably, but the mage deserved it because he/she completed the quest to have it. 
This post is not aimed directly at anyone, its just i have seen a lot of posts about this. Just wanted to state my thoughts. =)</TEXTAREA>
